515
00:26:57,866 --> 00:27:01,494
<i>My apartment is not made for kids
and this city is...</i>

516
00:27:02,704 --> 00:27:03,997
It's big.

517
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:08,960
But I do care about you, Mina,
and I promise I will check on you

518
00:27:09,044 --> 00:27:12,297
and make sure you have everything you need
with money or with, um,

519
00:27:12,380 --> 00:27:13,965
help with college applications.

520
00:27:14,049 --> 00:27:15,008
<i>So, basically...</i>

521
00:27:15,091 --> 00:27:16,926
<i>you don't have room
in your life for family.</i>

522
00:27:17,927 --> 00:27:19,137
<i>That's not what I said -</i>

523
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:21,639
No, that's what my father said about you.

524
00:27:23,433 --> 00:27:24,684
<i>I guess he was right.</i>

525
00:27:24,768 --> 00:27:25,769
[hangs up]

526
00:27:33,610 --> 00:27:36,780
I should have known that regular
anesthesia would be no match for...

527
00:27:45,372 --> 00:27:48,416
-The surgery was successful.
-It was.

528
00:27:49,167 --> 00:27:51,169
The burr hole relieved pressure,

529
00:27:51,252 --> 00:27:54,130
but the bleed had already
done too much damage.

530
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:56,216
He's not going to wake up.

531
00:27:57,509 --> 00:27:58,385
Okay.

532
00:27:59,886 --> 00:28:02,263
-I'm going to look for next of kin.
-Yeah.

533
00:28:05,266 --> 00:28:08,228
[PA announcements in background]

534
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:18,363
-You sure you got time for this?
-I got all the time in the world.

535
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:22,992
I started treating patients here the same
time as three other white residents,

536
00:28:23,076 --> 00:28:25,787
but you know how long it took
the department chair to learn my name?

537
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:27,705
Go ahead. Guess.

538
00:28:27,789 --> 00:28:31,042
Then I'll tell you how long it took
for him to stop calling me sister girl.

539
00:28:31,126 --> 00:28:34,963
I'm not a female surgeon.
I'm not a Puerto Rican surgeon.

540
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:37,424
I'm a surgeon and I'm one of the best.

541
00:28:37,507 --> 00:28:38,758
Nanny. [scoffs]

542
00:28:38,842 --> 00:28:42,178
Do you see children around me?
I mean, I'm wearing my badge. Hello?

543
00:28:42,262 --> 00:28:43,513
I'm not the translator.

544
00:28:43,596 --> 00:28:46,516
Listen, you don't have to speak Spanish
to me all the time. I speak English.

545
00:28:46,599 --> 00:28:47,600
It was misdiagnosed

546
00:28:47,684 --> 00:28:50,562
because the test didn't account for higher
creatine levels in Black folk.

547
00:28:50,645 --> 00:28:53,314
No matter how many times
I tell 'em, it's sickle cell,

548
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:55,775
white doctors always have me
take a drug test.

549
00:28:55,859 --> 00:28:57,652
Blamed it on insurance.
I'm like, "For real?"

550
00:28:57,736 --> 00:29:01,614
How does a white male gynecologist
know my pain better than I do?

551
00:29:01,698 --> 00:29:04,868
Four generations, US.
My newborn does not need a TB shot.

552
00:29:04,951 --> 00:29:08,538
I don't have a green card,
but I do have an American passport.

553
00:29:08,621 --> 00:29:10,582
The only border I ever cross
is New Jersey.

554
00:29:10,665 --> 00:29:13,626
I didn't go to school for 12 years
to learn how to smile more.

555
00:29:13,710 --> 00:29:17,464
When Dr. Reynolds made chair, do you
think people asked if his dad was proud?

556
00:29:17,547 --> 00:29:19,841
I see how they look at me
the moment they hear my voice.

557
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:22,719
He said we can't all be enlightened
as you about gender.

558
00:29:22,802 --> 00:29:25,388
Max, it's not really about
remembering my pronouns.

559
00:29:25,472 --> 00:29:28,099
It's about actually believing me
when I tell you who I am.

560
00:29:28,183 --> 00:29:30,018
I don't know how many of us there are.

561
00:29:30,101 --> 00:29:30,977
-AIDs.
-SIDs.

562
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:32,687
-Mixed race.
-Multiethnic.

563
00:29:32,771 --> 00:29:34,606
-None of the above.
-Indigenous?

564
00:29:34,689 --> 00:29:38,943
That can be from any part of the world.
I am a Native American.

565
00:29:39,027 --> 00:29:41,613
People call me many things. Bitch.

566
00:29:41,696 --> 00:29:43,615
-Chola.
-Coon. Spook.

567
00:29:43,698 --> 00:29:45,575
-Fragile.
-List goes on and on.

568
00:29:46,159 --> 00:29:47,035
Other.

569
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:48,286
-Other.
-Other.

570
00:29:51,289 --> 00:29:54,876
So I owe you a huge apology.

571
00:29:56,169 --> 00:29:57,212
I'm waiting.

572
00:29:58,588 --> 00:29:59,464
[sighs]

573
00:30:01,674 --> 00:30:02,550
I'm sorry.

574
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:05,220
I'm very sorry that I doubted you.

575
00:30:05,303 --> 00:30:06,638
No, worse. I...

576
00:30:07,388 --> 00:30:11,100
I decided that you were guilty before
you ever even set foot in my office

577
00:30:11,184 --> 00:30:12,310
and I am sorry.

578
00:30:13,478 --> 00:30:16,147
Seems judgmental for a doctor.

579
00:30:20,026 --> 00:30:21,152
I agree.

580
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:25,740
And I should have had more faith
in your progress, in you, honestly.

581
00:30:26,032 --> 00:30:30,912
Ollie is bad, but I would never lose
the game just to hurt him.

582
00:30:31,412 --> 00:30:32,455
Yeah, I believe you.

583
00:30:32,539 --> 00:30:34,123
So I told Luisa how to do it.

584
00:30:35,208 --> 00:30:36,793
You... You did what?

585
00:30:36,876 --> 00:30:39,254
I told Luisa how to get him alone,

586
00:30:40,004 --> 00:30:41,172
where no one would see,

587
00:30:41,756 --> 00:30:43,091
and I told her to use the door

588
00:30:43,174 --> 00:30:45,260
because it was the best way
for someone her size...

589
00:30:45,343 --> 00:30:47,345
No, no, Juliet, no, you can't do that.

590
00:30:47,428 --> 00:30:49,639
You can't teach kids to hurt other kids.

591
00:30:49,722 --> 00:30:51,850
I taught her how to defend herself.

592
00:30:51,933 --> 00:30:54,352
-That is not your job.
-But she's my friend.

593
00:31:00,984 --> 00:31:03,361
Do you really consider Luisa
to be your friend?

594
00:31:08,283 --> 00:31:09,158
Yes.

595
00:31:13,955 --> 00:31:14,831
Okay.

596
